---
description: Testing and verification requirements
alwaysApply: true
---

Testing is mandatory.

Every meaningful change must include the appropriate combination of:

- unit tests,
- contract tests,
- integration tests,
- smoke tests,
- replay tests,
- parity tests,
- end-to-end tests.

Critical flows include:

- authentication,
- event processing,
- point-in-time feature retrieval,
- decision orchestration,
- human review,
- order submission,
- cancel and replace,
- partial fills,
- reconciliation,
- ledger booking,
- P&L,
- kill switch,
- restricted-list enforcement.

Testing rules:

- Test observable behavior.
- Keep tests deterministic.
- Avoid sleep-based synchronization.
- Avoid unseeded randomness.
- Do not over-mock domain behavior.
- Test error paths.
- Test retries and idempotency.
- Test stale and missing data.
- Test rollback and recovery when relevant.
- Test same input + same config = same output.

Before completion run:

- format
- lint
- typecheck
- unit tests
- relevant integration tests
- relevant smoke or e2e tests

Never say a test passed unless it actually ran.
